<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Http_Client is locale dependent and it doesn't work on locales where decimal symbol is represented by coma sign instead of dot. When I set the locale to pl_PL (Polish) Zend_Http_Client tried set this header:</p>

<p>{quote}GET / HTTP/1,1{quote}</p>

<p>instead of:</p>

<p>{quote}GET / HTTP/1.1{quote}</p>

<p>so I got the 400 response (Bad request).</p>

<p>This affects all classes which utiilize http_client eg. Zend_Feed.</p>

<p>It could be resolved by changing HTTP protocol versions value types from float to string. Then value won't be affected by current locale.</p>

    </div>
